Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu has picked the nomination form of the All Progressives Congress at the National Secretariat of the party in Abuja ahead of the APC's primary and governorship election in Edo State. Governor Godwin Obaseki had been at loggerheads with National Chairman of the party, Adams Oshiomhole, and the emergence of Ize-Iyamu may pose some of form of threat to his second term ambition. 